Package org.apache.ruples.immutable

package org.apache.ruples.immutable
This package contains the immutable Ruple records, from Ruple1 to Ruple12. These records represent tuples of various sizes (1 to 12 elements) and are designed to hold data in an immutable and type-safe manner. Each Ruple is a fixed-size collection of values, which can be accessed in a structured way, making it suitable for use cases where immutability and type safety are required.

The records in this package are:

  • Ruple1 - A tuple of one element.
  • Ruple2 - A tuple of two elements.
  • Ruple3 - A tuple of three elements.
  • Ruple4 - A tuple of four elements.
  • Ruple5 - A tuple of five elements.
  • Ruple6 - A tuple of six elements.
  • Ruple7 - A tuple of seven elements.
  • Ruple8 - A tuple of eight elements.
  • Ruple9 - A tuple of nine elements.
  • Ruple10 - A tuple of ten elements.
  • Ruple11 - A tuple of eleven elements.
  • Ruple12 - A tuple of twelve elements.

These records are commonly used when working with fixed-size collections of data, where the number of elements is known in advance, and the immutability of the data is a key requirement.
